- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves translating graph algorithms from one representation to another.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper involves expressing graph algorithms in a linear algebraic language.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the GraphBLAS interface is used in some machine learning applications.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is unlikely but cannot be completely ruled out as the paper deals with graph algorithms.
